{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04404/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04404"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:44:04"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A group of spectators sit watching the fashion show."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04404","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04404"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/canvas/1/93e6deab-e009-45fa-86fe-956816b89d84","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:09:33.732Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Production designer Mark Tildesley notes how the Reynolds’s London house plays many roles for the characters: “‘The House of Woodcock is a place of work but it's also a theatrical space, where clients are beguiled and made to feel glorious and wonderful as if they were on stage,’ says Tildesley. ‘Below this world — the downstairs to all the splendor upstairs — is a kind of sweatshop, where seamstresses make costumes and prepare for shows, or for private clients to come in for fittings. It's a functioning business with a kind of heightened theatricality to it, with hard work going on behind the scenes that becomes worrying, difficult, and meticulous. It's a showroom, very elegant and simple, like a ballet backdrop’” (“About the Production,” 22).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04404/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:102.07267833109017,80.67294751009429,405.7065948855989,246.78331090174964"}}}]}]}]}